-- Santander to buy GE consumer financing business in Northern Europe
-- By Paul Day
-- Mon Jun 23, 2014 02:43AM EDT
-- None



MADRID, June 23 (Reuters) - Spain's largest bank Santander <SAN.MC> said on Monday it has agreed to acquire GE Money Bank, GE Capital's <GE.N> consumer finance business in Sweden, Norway and Denmark, for 700 million euros ($950.29 million).

The deal is expected to close in the second half of 2014 and will have an impact of 8 basis points on Santander's core capital, the bank said in a statement to the stock market regulator.